Chapter 2: Your work

2.1 Describing job roles
Learn to talk about different roles within a company

Our manager asks senior staff to help junior employees.

junior
A junior employee has a lower position in a company.

senior
A senior employee has a higher position in a company.

A senior position ("senior" position) is above 
a junior position ("junior" position).

Alvaro is new to the company. He's a junior employee.
Ruth has worked here for ten years. She's a senior employee.

a director
A director is the top position in a department.






































